FT  16 OCT 92 / UK Company News: Compromise in C&amp;J Clark row
C&amp;J Clark, the private shoe manufacturer and retailer, yesterday won a
reprieve in the boardroom wrangle which threatened to unseat the chairman
and a non-executive director, writes Peggy Hollinger.
After days of intense talks, the 11-strong board reached a compromise to
adjourn today's egm until April.
